code.originalText: From any of: Wound, Genital mucus, CSF, Aspirate, Periton Fl, Pleur Fl, Vag, Throat, Synov Fl, Eye, Ear, Bronch, Dialisis fl, Fld, Nose, Pus, Cervix, Genital fl, Urthera, Sputum, Stool, Urine, Tissue

Issue: The code for the requested susceptibility panel does not appear here as might be expected. Instead, it appears in a Battery that is a subordinate part of this Cluster. The reason is that RMIM POLB_RM004000 implies that isolates should always be associated with a SpecimenObservationCluster, and the Subject of the Cluster is always the Isolate. Cluster.code then confirms that the isolate has been identified.
